align:16d92a28-4d0a-4bbf-8433-09ca7472861b a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:b0f22bab-f0d6-439d-9c58-dbd7af7c22e5 ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts refer to the realization of something abstract (algorithm/model) into executable form. The AIDOC definition explicitly mentions 'executable software', while ml-onto's description is missing, but the label strongly suggests a similar meaning. They aren’t *exactly* interchangeable – one focuses on algorithms specifically, and the other is more general – hence closeMatch rather than exactMatch."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:SoftwareImplementation ;
    align:target <http://www.w3.org/ns/mls#Implementation> .

align:4c7c5b61-457d-49d4-8df4-496c8ffd4dfd a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:b0f22bab-f0d6-439d-9c58-dbd7af7c22e5 ;
    align:confidence "0.95"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts share the same label and a highly similar description focusing on assessing performance, robustness, and accuracy of models. The lack of a description for ml-onto doesn't detract from the strong lexical and semantic overlap."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:exactMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:ModelEvaluation ;
    align:target <http://www.w3.org/ns/mls#ModelEvaluation> .

align:5f5ccc33-b0f1-4a3a-b6b6-3d66624859b4 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:b0f22bab-f0d6-439d-9c58-dbd7af7c22e5 ;
    align:confidence "0.95"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts share the same label and a very similar (though one is missing) description indicating they represent the same core idea of a 'Dataset'. The high lexical similarity supports this."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:exactMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:Dataset ;
    align:target <http://www.w3.org/ns/mls#Dataset> .

align:b7abe072-1691-49b2-bb80-6498ba6a14f9 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:b0f22bab-f0d6-439d-9c58-dbd7af7c22e5 ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts represent an 'Agent', and the lexical similarity is high (0.608). However, AIDOC explicitly frames this agent within the *AI lifecycle*, making it a specialized type of Agent. The ml-onto concept, using FOAF's definition, is more general. Therefore, they aren’t exact matches but are close enough to be interchangeable in many AI-related contexts."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:AIAgent ;
    align:target foaf:Agent .

align:d77a1d17-a899-42d6-a7cb-3f79fe993f4b a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:b0f22bab-f0d6-439d-9c58-dbd7af7c22e5 ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts refer to a computational representation used for tasks – 'AI Model' explicitly within the AI domain and 'Model' more generally (as indicated by the ml-onto namespace suggesting Machine Learning). The descriptions are highly similar in intent, though AIDOC specifies *how* the model is used. They aren’t identical enough for exactMatch, but sufficiently close to be interchangeable in many ML/AI contexts."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:AIModel ;
    align:target <http://www.w3.org/ns/mls#Model> .

align:e49519eb-d0c8-4446-ac7e-401a80a00fb6 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:b0f22bab-f0d6-439d-9c58-dbd7af7c22e5 ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "The AIDOC 'Modality' focuses specifically on *how* an AI system is delivered – a deployment characteristic. The ml-onto 'Data Modality' describes the *type of data itself*. While related (an AI system will *use* data modalities), the ml-onto concept is broader, encompassing all forms of data representation, not just those relevant to AI system provision. Therefore, AIDOC’s modality is a specific instance within the broader scope of Data Modality."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:broadMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:Modality ;
    align:target <http://w3id.org/mlso/DataModality> .

aidoc:AIAgent skos:closeMatch foaf:Agent .

aidoc:AIModel skos:closeMatch <http://www.w3.org/ns/mls#Model> .

aidoc:Dataset skos:exactMatch <http://www.w3.org/ns/mls#Dataset> .

aidoc:Modality skos:broadMatch <http://w3id.org/mlso/DataModality> .

aidoc:ModelEvaluation skos:exactMatch <http://www.w3.org/ns/mls#ModelEvaluation> .

aidoc:SoftwareImplementation skos:closeMatch <http://www.w3.org/ns/mls#Implementation> .

